{What move would Black like to play here in order to improve one of their pieces? Can we stop this move from happening?} 14. c5 $16 {[%csl Rb7] Black wanted to play ...[c5] in order to open up their bishop to attack our rook and also put pressure on our pawn center. By playing [c5], we are preventing their idea and gaining a bigger space advantage of our own. The only downside to this move is that we weaken the [d5]-square, which Black's knight might exploit later; however, this drawback is a small price to pay for blocking Black's bishop on the [a8]-[h1] diagonal.} (14. Rae1 $6 {It seems like a reasonable move to activate our final piece, but it doesn't prevent Black's idea.} c5 {, Black has opened their bishop.} 15. d5 {, trying to take advantage of the pin along the e-file doesn't work. Following} Nf6 16. R4e2 exd5 17. Rxe8+ Nxe8 {∞ , Black has been able to trade a pair of rooks and eliminate our space advantage.}) *

