{Black has just played 21...Kg7. What would they like to play next move and can White prevent this?} 22. Qe3 $1 {[%csl Rh6][%cal Gh7h6,Ge3h6] Black wanted to play ...[h6] to kick the bishop away from the active [g5]-square. By playing [Qe3], White now has much better control of the [h6]-square and effectively prevents Black's idea. This means that the bishop will be able to stay on the [g5]-square and continue to create trouble for Black.} (22. Rad1 $6 {was played in the game, but this didn't prevent Black's idea. After} h6 23. Bc1 {∞ , White is still a bit better with the bishop pair, but the bishops are pretty inactive right now.}) 22... Nc4 {Black might try to kick away White's queen.} 23. Qc1 $16 {[%csl Rc4][%cal Gb2b3] Keeping the queen on the diagonal towards [h6]. Next, White's idea is to play [b3] to kick the knight away and [h5] to generate threats against Black's king.} *

