{White has just played 17.h3. What is their idea and can we prevent it?} 17... h4 $17 {[%csl Rg3][%cal Gh4g3,Gg2g4] White wanted to play [g4] in order to gain more space on the kingside and open up lines on that half of the board. By playing ...[h4], Black has neutralized White's [g4] plan, rendering it less attractive due to the looming en passant threat. Also, since the g-pawn cannot move forward without being exchanged, it means that White's [f4]-pawn is now also weak, just like their [d5]-pawn. If the g-pawn is traded off, then White will be left with isolated h- and f-pawns.} (17... O-O $2 {Castling doesn't work against White's idea. After} 18. g4 {∞ , by gaining space on the kingside, White can look to open up files for attacking chances towards our king.}) *

