{Black has a weak pawn on [c7] that they would like to get rid of. What would they like to play next move and how can we prevent this?} 1. b4 $14 {[%csl Rc5,Rc7][%cal Ge1d3,Gb1d2,Gd2b3] White can prevent Black from playing ...[c5]. If Black is not able to trade off their c-pawn, then it will be stuck as a long-term weakness, which will need to be defended by pieces for the rest of the game.} (1. Nd3 {⩲ is another possible option for preventing ...[c5].}) (1. Nd2 $2 {doesn't prevent Black from executing their idea. After} c5 {∞ , Black is able to advance and eventually trade off their weak c-pawn, which helps their position a lot.}) *

