{What move would Black like to play in order to eliminate White's bishop pair? How can we prevent that from happening?} 1. Rb1 $1 {[%csl Rb5][%cal Gd7b5,Gb1b5] We prevent Black from playing ...[Bb5] and target their [b7]-pawn. We don't mind losing the [a3]-pawn since it will come at the cost of our pieces gaining a lot of activity.} (1. Bd3 $2 {A developing move like this doesn't address Black's idea.} Bb5 {∞ and Black is able to trade off our light-squared bishop, which is quite beneficial for them.}) 1... Qxa3 $2 2. Bb4 Qa4 3. Rh3 $18 {[%csl Re7,Rf7][%cal Gh3f3,Gf3a3] Black is in big trouble here, since their king is weak and White's pieces are super active.} *

