{Black wants to play ...[d5] to gain a space advantage in the center. How can we discourage this?} 19. c4 $1 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gc4d5,Ge4d5] We gain more space ourselves, while also limiting Black's opportunities to play ...[d5] under favorable circumstances.} (19. Rad1 $6 {A slow move would allow Black to execute their plan.} d5 20. exd5 cxd5 21. c4 $2 {This pawn advance is now too late.} d4 {∓ , Black gains a bigger space advantage and has a good position. Our knight has limited options and no clearly advantageous squares to move to.}) 19... d5 {Black can try the advance anyways, but we're prepared for it now.} 20. exd5 {We welcome trading as many pawns as possible when we have the bishop pair.} cxd5 21. cxd5 Nexd5 22. b3 $16 {[%csl Re5] Black has a space advantage after the pawn trades, but their isolated [e5]-pawn and our strong pair of bishops give White a good position.} *

