{Here White has a good knight vs. Black's bad dark-squared bishop. What square would this knight like to be on and how can we maneuver it there?} 20. Nh2 {[%csl Rf5][%cal Gh2g4,Gg4e3,Ge3f5] White's knight is en route to the [f5]-square.} Bd6 21. Ng4 Kg7 22. Ne3 Qf6 23. Nf5+ $18 {[%csl Gf5,Rd6] White has a huge advantage due to their great minor piece vs. Black's bad one. The knight also excels at pressuring several points of vulnerability in Black's half of the board while remaining well-supported.} *

