[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2133654360356882"]

{Here, we can see a second example defining an unsafe king. Black's king has walked (not castled) from [e8] to [c8]. Although the king has decent pawn coverage, its safety is compromised by the lack of castling, which would have provided additional protection and a more secure position. As a result, the king's unconventional move to [c8] makes it more vulnerable to potential attacks compared to White's safely castled king on [g1]. Notably, White's [e5]-bishop and [g3]-queen are lining up towards the [c7]-pawn in front of Black's king. This may become a target for White as the game progresses. You can see how the game continued by clicking here.} 1. Z0 *

