{So we've seen two examples of positions where one side has a king safety advantage compared to the opponent. How can we gain this type of advantage in the first place? Here are a few methods: Advance one of our pawns forward to provoke a weakness around the opponent's king. Trade pieces to open up the pawn coverage in front of the opponent's king. Sacrifice a piece or play in a way that draws the opponent's king out into the open.} 1. Z0 *

[Event "Seal the Deal: How to Gain and Convert Middlegame Advantages"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2) King Safety"]
[Black "King Safety − Blueprint to Convert"]
[Result "*"]
[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2133654360373268"]

{Once we've weakened the opponent's king protection and gained the king safety advantage, then the main plan is to attack the weakened king and look to checkmate them or gain other advantages as we attack. The blueprint looks like this: ➝ Weaken the opponent's king ➝ Open up files and diagonals towards the opponent's king ➝ Maneuver our pieces towards the opponent's king ➝ Gain other advantages or checkmate the opponent's king. The blueprint for this specific advantage is pretty straightforward, but other ones will be less obvious. Let's move on to a few examples where we will see this blueprint in action.} 1. Z0 *

