{White has managed to create pressure against Black's king. What is the best way to play from here?} 39. Bxg7+ $1 {This wins material in a more dangerous way compared to trading queens.} ({After} 39. Qxe8 $6 Nxe8 40. Nxf7+ Kg8 41. Nd8 {± , White ends up ahead a pawn, but we can do better than this. Keeping the queens on the board would have been more dangerous for Black.}) 39... Kxg7 {In the game Black walked into checkmate.} (39... Bxg7 40. Qxd6 {+- and White is ahead a pawn with a big advantage due to Black's king remaining unsafe. It's very helpful that we've kept the queens on the board to take advantage of this!}) 40. Qb2+ $1 {Some nice geometry to go from [b8] to [b2] and attack [g7].} Kg6 41. Qf6+ Kh5 42. Bf3# {A nice checkmate finish!} 1-0

