{How did Magnus work to open up White's kingside?} 13... h5 $17 {[%csl Rh8][%cal Gh5g4] This pawn break has the intention of trading pawns on [g4] in order to open the h-file for the rook. Even if White sidesteps this by playing [g5], then their kingside is still weakened and the [f5]-square becomes an outpost for Black's knight.} (13... f5 $6 {This is a different pawn break to open the kingside but has the drawback of blocking the [g6]-bishop. After} 14. g5 {∞ , the bishop is shut in by the [f5]-pawn and the knight doesn't have a great square to maneuver towards.}) *

