{White has managed to keep the kingside somewhat closed, but Carlsen found another way to crack open White's kingside structure. What did he play?} 20... f6 {[%csl Rg3][%cal Gf6g5,Gb8g3] White cannot avoid more files and diagonals opening up on the kingside.} 21. h4 {Trying to keep the [g5]-pawn held in place.} e5 {Another pawn break that finally blasts open the kingside.} (21... fxg5 22. hxg5 Rf5 {-+ is another strong way of playing. White cannot save the [g5]-pawn without losing the [f4]-pawn in the process.}) 22. f5 {White is really trying to keep things shut down, but it doesn't work.} exd4+ {Discovered check allows Black to capture on [d4]. White's position is falling apart.} (22... e4+ {+ -+ is also good.}) 23. Kh3 Qc8 {[%csl Rf5][%cal Gc8h3]} (23... fxg5 $1 {was even stronger.} 24. fxg6 (24. Bxg5 Bxf5+ 25. Rxf5 Qc8 {-+ , Black recaptures the rook with the queen due to the pin and mates soon.}) 24... Qc8+ {+ -+ and White is mated soon.}) 24. Qf3 fxg5 {[%csl Rf5][%cal Gf8f3,Gc8h3] There are too many pins on the [f5]-pawn, and White's king is very unsafe.} 25. hxg5 Rxf5 $19 {[%csl Rh3][%cal Gc8h3] White resigned due to all of the upcoming discovered checks.} 0-1

