{White is ahead a piece. What is the simplest way to work towards converting the material advantage?} 22. Bd1 {[%csl Rg4][%cal Gg3g5] Looking to trade bishops due to the pin on the g-file.} ({Trading rooks on the f-file first is fine too:} 22. Rxf8+ Rxf8 23. Bd1 {+- .}) 22... h5 23. Bxg4 hxg4 24. Ne2 (24. Rxf8+ Rxf8 25. Rf1 {+-}) 24... Qh6 25. Rxf8+ {Trading more pieces along the open f-file.} Rxf8 26. Rf1 {Open files are a very common location for piece trades.} g6 27. Rxf8+ Kxf8 28. Qf4+ {[%csl Rh6][%cal Gf4h6,Gf4f8] The queens come off the board as well.} (28. Qxg4 $6 {allows Black to keep the queens on the board with some counterplay. After} Qxe3+ 29. Kf1 Qd3 {+- , White is still completely winning, but why allow the queen to stay on the board and cause counterplay?}) 28... Kg7 29. Qxh6+ Kxh6 30. Kf2 {Black resigned due to being in a lost endgame where they're down a piece.} 1-0

