{We're ahead a pawn but Black has active pieces and pressure on our uncastled king. How should we play here to shut down some of Black's activity?} 17. f3 $1 {[%cal Gf3g4] Pushing back the light-squared bishop, which was putting pressure on our [e2]-pawn. We are not in a rush to castle kingside since our king would be unsafe there.} (17. O-O $2 {This castles right into trouble.} Be5 $1 {Looking to kick away our strong knight.} 18. Qd2 Nd4 {, threatening to capture on [f4], as then [e2] with the queen being overloaded on [d2] will be in trouble.} 19. f3 Bxf4 20. Bxf4 Nb3 21. Qd1 Rxf4 22. Qxb3 Bh3 {∞ . This position is very messy with a lot of continued pressure around our king. The [h4]-pawn is hanging and we're in a tricky situation.}) 17... Be5 {[%cal Ge5f4] Black ignores our threat and attacks the [f4]-knight instead.} 18. Qd2 {It's important to keep the knight defended. We maintain the threat on the [g4]-bishop.} (18. fxg4 $2 {Making this capture allows Black to trade off our active pieces and take over the piece activity advantage themselves.} Bxf4 19. Bxf4 Rxf4 20. gxh5 Qg4 {∞ , Black has a lot of counterplay and very active pieces.}) 18... Nd4 $5 {Black decides to sacrifice a piece and goes all-in on the attack relying on their piece activity and safer king.} ({After} 18... Bf5 19. e4 {, we can continue to push Black's bishop backwards.} Be6 20. Nxe6 Bg3+ 21. Kd1 Qxe6 22. Ne2 Be5 23. f4 {+- , Black's attack has been pushed back and now it's White who can go on the offensive.}) 19. fxg4 Qxg4 20. O-O $18 {Only now do we castle. The rook on [f1] defends the [f4]-knight while our king defends the [g2]-bishop. Black's attack is starting to run out of steam and our extra piece will help us to win the game as it progresses.} (20. e3 $4 {looks reasonable, but leaving our king in the center now backfires.} Bxf4 21. Bxf4 Rxf4 $1 {Sacrificing more material in order to open up the e-file.} 22. exf4 Nef5+ 23. Ne4 Qg3+ 24. Kf1 Ne3+ 25. Kg1 Nf3# {. A beautiful checkmate that we would rather not fall into!}) (20. Rf1 $4 {defends the knight but doesn't save the bishop on [g2]:} Bxf4 21. Bxf4 Qxg2 {-+ .}) *

