{Black is attacking our queen and looking to push it away from defending the [f4]-knight. How should we respond?} 21. Qd1 {[%cal Gd1b3] Defending [f4] wasn't possible but we can counterattack the [b3]-knight.} (21. Qe3 $4 {This defends the knight but is a huge blunder.} Bd4 {, we've just gotten our queen pinned and lost.}) 21... Bxf4 22. Bxf4 Rxf4 23. Qxb3 {The piece exchanges have only helped White. Black's attack is now much less dangerous with less pieces on the board.} Rxf1+ 24. Rxf1 Qd4+ 25. Rf2 {Walking into a pin, but White would rather not move the king to the h-file and allow Black to capture the [h4]-pawn with check.} Rf8 26. Ne4 Rxf2 27. Nxf2 $18 {White has an extra piece with a big advantage.} *

