{How can White win a pawn from here?} 10. g4 {We may recognize that the [d5]-pawn is attacked once and defended once. If we could get rid of the knight on [f6], then we could win the pawn. In order to do that we can use our g-pawn as a bulldozer. First, we kick the bishop backwards.} Bg6 11. g5 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Gg5f6] Next is the knight.} Nh5 12. Nxd5 $14 {And now that the knight is off the [f6]-square, we're able to capture the undefended [d5]-pawn! Black does have some compensation here revolving around our slightly exposed king, but the extra pawn is still nice for White to have.} *

