{Black was able to equalize the material but landed themselves in this tricky position with their knight on [e6] being pinned. How can White win material from here?} 20. Qg4 $1 {[%csl Re6,Rg5][%cal Gg4g5,Gg4e6] Not only attacking the pinned knight a second time but also putting pressure on Black's bishop. There is not a good way for Black to avoid losing a piece here.} Rae8 {This defends the knight a second time, but the queen on [e7] is still overloaded.} 21. Bxe6+ Qxe6 22. Qxg5 $18 {White has won a piece and went on to win the game later.} *

