{Earlier in the game Black had sacrificed a rook for a minor piece plus pawn. White ends up with a good advantage here as long as we play against Black's plans and ideas. What does Black want to play here and how can White play against that plan?} 22. Re1 $1 {[%csl Re5][%cal Ge6e5] Black wants to play ...[e5] in the near future. This would allow them to mobilize their central pawn duo and open up the light-squared bishop. The best way for White to play is to prevent Black's plan in the first place! Next, we can look to advance the knight forward into the weak [e5]-square.} Qd6 {[%cal Ge6e5] Black gets their queen away from the sights of the [f2]-rook and still wants to play ...[e5] soon.} 23. Ne5 $1 {Planting the knight on [e5], which is nicely blockading Black's weak backward [e6]-pawn. Now their pawns cannot advance easily and White has grown their advantage.} *

