{White has grown their advantage over the last few moves by solidifying the [e5]-knight and advancing the pawn to [g5]. How can we finish off the game from here with a tactic?} 28. Nxd7 {Normally, we might not be in a rush to make this exchange of pieces since our knight was much stronger than the bad bishop on [d7]. However, in this case, there is a tactical reason to make the trade.} Rxd7 29. Rxe6 $1 {[%csl Rb8][%cal Gb6b8,Gb6e6] This is the important follow-up to see. Black's queen is getting deflected from defending the back rank.} Qxe6 {Other moves would also leave Black in a terrible position.} 30. Qb8+ $18 {Mate on the back rank follows after Black throws away their pieces one-by-one to deal with the check.} 1-0

