{How can we play to gain the best version of a long-term advantage?} 22. Nxf7 $1 {We have a nice tactic available. We want to clear the [e5]-square for our rook to access.} Kxf7 23. Re5 $18 {[%csl Rc5,Rf5][%cal Ge5f5,Ge5c5] Black will lose one of their bishops. In order to avoid being down a pawn they should play ...[Bxa3], but after we recapture on [a3] with the rook, then we'll have the bishop pair and continue to pressure Black's [f5]-bishop and [a5]-pawn.} *

