{How can White gain the bishop pair advantage?} 11. g4 {First, kicking the bishop back to [g6].} Bg6 12. Ne5 {[%csl Rg6][%cal Ge5g6] Now that the bishop has nowhere to run to, White will trade their knight for it next move.} (12. Nh4 $2 {This specific square runs into trouble for White due to the [e7]-bishop eyeing the knight on [h4].} Nxg4 $1 {Opening a discovered attack on White's knight.} 13. Nxg6 Nxe3 14. Nxh8 Nxf1 15. Kxf1 Nd7 {⩱ , Black will win the trapped knight on [h8] within a few moves. White will need to sacrifice their knight for the [f7]-pawn soon, which will result in equal material, but Black's pawn structure will still be better and White will not have the bishop pair advantage.}) 12... Nbd7 13. Nxg6 {[%csl Ge3,Gg2] White has gained the bishop pair advantage.} *

