{Black has just played ...[a6]. What is their idea, and can we stop it?} 10. a4 $16 {[%cal Gb7b5,Ga4b5] Black wanted to play ...[b5] in order to chip away at our [c4]-pawn. It is important for us to take action quickly to prevent this idea so that we can keep our center as secure as possible. Without ...[b5] being possible, the only real pawn break that Black has left over is ...[e6].} (10. O-O $6 {An autopilot move like this would allow Black to execute their intended pawn break.} b5 $1 {doesn't lose a pawn due to our need to keep the [e4]-pawn defended. White's position is still better but why allow this pawn break in the first place?} 11. cxb5 $2 axb5 12. Nxb5 $2 Nxb5 13. Bxb5 Nxe4 {∓ . All of a sudden Black is better since our center is crumbling and their pieces are waking up.}) *

