{Black has just played ...[Qg7], offering a trade of queens. How should White respond?} 22. Qd2 $16 {It's important to keep the queens on the board with the goal of using it to help with an attack later. If the queens get traded, then part of White's advantage disappears.} ({After} 22. Qxg7+ $2 Kxg7 {∞ , White still has the space advantage, but without queens on the board it becomes easier for Black to navigate the position. They get access to the [f4]-square for their knight and don't have to worry about any king safety issues anymore.}) (22. Qg5 {± , moving back to [g5] or [c1] is also fine. Make sure you don't retreat the queen to [e3] and walk into a pin on the e-file though!} Rxb2 $4 {Black cannot win the [b2]-pawn since we would get the [d6]-pawn in return:} 23. Rxb2 Qxb2 24. Nxd6 {+- .}) *

