{Now that the [e5]-pawn is secure then what's the next step? There are usually two things we can work towards when we have a space advantage. One option is that we can look to advance our pawns forward to gain more space, move further into the opponent's territory, and potentially create problems for them. The other option is to play on the side of the board where we have our space advantage and look to maneuver our pieces in that direction. Usually, we will want to work towards a pawn break that will create weaknesses or open up files/diagonals into our opponent's territory. Since the first option is difficult to accomplish here (our [e5]-pawn cannot move forward) , then we should look to play on the flank or side of the board where we have the space advantage. In this case, we have more space on the kingside (the [e5]-pawn is cramping Black over there) and we can look to play on that side of the board. This also makes sense from the process of elimination because it is actually Black who has the space advantage on the queenside right now ...[b5] and ...[d5] pawns.} 15. h4 $1 {[%csl Rg6,Rg8][%cal Gh4h5] An important part of White's kingside play is working towards a pawn break that can create problems. By working towards [h4]-[h5] and potentially capturing on [g6], we can look to weaken Black's kingside, which improves our attacking chances.} Bb7 16. h5 Rc8 {Black continues to play on the queenside part of the board, but they haven't done anything we need to be concerned about yet.} (16... gxh5 $4 {Capturing the pawn is suicidal since it opens the diagonal for the [c2]-bishop towards the [h7]-pawn.} 17. Ng5 h6 18. Bh7+ Kf8 19. Nxf7 $1 {Sacrifices like this need to be calculated, but tactics tend to work out for the player who has the advantage in the first place.} Kxf7 20. Qxh5+ Ke7 21. Bg3 {, threatening a check on [h4].} Kf8 22. Qf3+ {and Black cannot avoid losing material.} Nf6 23. exf6 Qxf6 24. Bd6+ Kf7 25. Qh5+ {+- , mate comes next.}) 17. Qd2 $18 {White isn't in a rush to capture on [g6] just yet. The pawn might go to [h6] in some situations too. White still understands that if Black captures on [h5], then it would be very dangerous for them.} *

