{White has a space advantage in the center/kingside due to the [e5]-pawn. How should White make use of this advantage?} 13. h4 {[%csl Rg6,Rg8][%cal Gh4h5] We can begin to push on the kingside with the plan to gain more space and provoke weaknesses.} Rfe8 {Opening the [f8]-square for the knight.} (13... h6 $6 {prevents the pawn from getting to [h6], but the knight will get pushed back to the corner of the board. Following} 14. h5 Nh8 15. Bf4 {± , Black's knight looks absolutely silly on the [h8]-square and it will take some time for it to get back in the game.}) 14. h5 $14 {[%csl Rg7,Rg8][%cal Gc1f4,Gh5g6,Gg1h1,Ge1g1,Gb1d2,Gh5h6] The knight has to retreat and we can follow this up with [Bf4], [Nbd2], [Kh1], and [Rg1] and continue playing on the kingside. We may also play [h6] in some situations to attack Black's [g7]-pawn and weaken their kingside.} *

