{How can we play to gain the best version of a long-term advantage?} 6. e4 $18 {Simply gaining the biggest space advantage possible in the center before Black gets to put a pawn in the center themselves. If Black plays ...[Nf6], then we can play [e5] to kick the knight and gain more space. If they play ...[d5], then we may trade pawns to open the e-file for quick pressure on Black's uncastled king.} (6. c4 $6 {also gains more space but gives Black the chance to stop us from pushing [e4].} Nf6 {± , White is still in great shape here, but getting the pawn to [e4] immediately is even better.}) *

