[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2133654361962634"]

{Here we have another position for us to consider. Where are the weaknesses here? White has doubled pawns on the c-file and an isolated pawn on [a3]. Which of these pawn weaknesses can be attacked and targeted the easiest? It tends to be the case with doubled pawns that the front or forward of the two pawns is usually the easier one to attack. This is because the front pawn is easier to target with our rooks, whereas the pawn in the back cannot be hit with rooks. For this reason, Black should aim to attack the [c4]-pawn with multiple pieces in this position you will solve this puzzle later.} 10... Z0 *

[Event "Seal the Deal: How to Gain and Convert Middlegame Advantages"]
[Site "?"]
