[Result "0-1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "1rr3k1/5pp1/p3pnp1/3p4/3P1qP1/PNP4P/Q4P2/2R2RK1 b - - 0 23"]
[PlyCount "19"]
[GameId "2133654361999503"]

{How can Black look to take advantage of White's pawn weaknesses?} 23... Ne4 $1 {[%csl Rc3][%cal Ge4c3] White's knight moved away from defending the [e4]-square so Black jumps right in. Now the pawn on [c3] is hit a second time.} 24. f3 {White realizes that they can't hold the position together and this allows Black to win material quickly.} (24. Qb2 {, White could try to defend the [c3]-pawn, but now the weakness on the kingside can be exploited.} Ng5 {, attacking the [h3]-pawn and aiming at the [f3]-square.} 25. Kg2 Qf3+ {+ -+ and White will get checkmated soon.}) 24... Nxc3 25. Qb2 Rxb3 $1 {Not the only good move, but it does result in Black winning more material.} 26. Qxb3 Qg3+ 27. Kh1 Qxh3+ 28. Kg1 Ne2+ 29. Kf2 Qh2+ 30. Ke3 Nxc1 {Black is ahead a bunch of material with a winning attack.} 31. Qd1 Rc3+ 32. Qd3 Rxd3# {Black did a great job of creating a situation where they could attack White's weak pawn on [b2] by opening up the file towards it. After White made the mistake of advancing their pawn off [b2], then Black created a new weakness on [c3]. Later Black won this pawn and crashed through on the kingside on top of things. A nice game!} 0-1

