{How can we play to gain the best version of a long-term advantage?} 22... bxc4 $17 {[%csl Rb2][%cal Ge7b7,Gc8c6,Gc6b6,Gf8b8] Recapturing with the pawn is best. This is because it opens the b-file towards White's weak backward pawn on [b2]. Black can work towards using the rooks and queen on the b-file to attack this pawn and tie down White's pieces to defend it. One way of doing this is ...[Rc6]-[b6], ...[Qb7] and ...[Rb8].} (22... Rxc4 {⩱ was played in the game and Black still won later, but recapturing with the b-pawn is much better.}) 0-1

