{In regards to gaining advantages, I have listed them here as one informational reference. This is a handy list of everything covered in the course, all in one place. Hope it helps! 1. How to gain a king safety advantage: Advance one of our pawns forward to provoke a weakness around the opponent's king. Trade pieces to open up the pawn coverage in front of the opponent's king. Sacrifice a piece or play in a way that draws the opponent's king out into the open. 2. How to gain a material advantage: Capture free material due to opponent's mistake or blunder. Execute a tactic. Accept a sacrifice from the opponent opening gambit or they willingly gave up material later in the game. 3. How to gain a bishop pair advantage: Actively look to trade one of your knights for one of the opponent's bishops. Your opponent willingly traded off one of their bishops for one of your knights. 4. How to gain a space advantage: From the opening phase some openings give one player more of a space advantage compared to other openings. Advance your pawns forward while the opponent is not doing the same. Use pawn breaks to exchange off your opponent's pawns and thus lower their space control which, in turn, gives you the advantage. 5. How to gain a pawn weakness advantage: Trade pieces in a way that creates a weak pawn structure. Use pawn breaks to provoke weaknesses. Attack pawns with pieces in order to provoke weaknesses.} 1. Z0 *

