{In this example, we will see a situation where we can gain a space advantage and then transform this into a material advantage after a few mistakes from Black. To begin with, Black has not done a good job of protecting their central [d5]-pawn with another pawn. White can take swift action to gain a huge space advantage here, to begin with.} 4. cxd5 {Trading off Black's central pawn when they have to recapture with a piece is strong. If Black could have recaptured with a pawn, then we may not have been in a rush to make the pawn trade.} Nxd5 ({Capturing with the queen doesn't help much:} 4... Qxd5 5. Nc3 Qa5 6. Bd2 {+- and White will play [e4] in the near future with a big advantage.}) 5. e4 {Expanding in the center and gaining space with tempo is rarely a bad idea.} Nf6 6. Nc3 {[%csl Gd4,Ge4] White has both of their central pawns defended well and it is difficult for Black to attack them effectively.} Bg4 $6 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gg4d1] This pin looks reasonable to put more pressure on the [d4]-pawn, but it ends up backfiring quickly.} 7. d5 $1 {[%cal Gd5c6] Advancing further in the center and kicking the knight.} Ne5 {[%csl Rf3][%cal Gg4d1] It looks like Black is going to succeed in trading some pieces off next move by capturing our pinned knight on [f3]. However...} 8. Nxe5 $3 {White can sacrifice the queen in order to convert the space advantage into a material advantage using some nice tactical ideas.} Bxd1 9. Bb5+ {[%csl Re8][%cal Gb5e8] Black has trouble blocking the check on the diagonal.} c6 (9... Nd7 10. Bxd7+ Qxd7 11. Nxd7 Kxd7 12. Kxd1 {+- and White emerges ahead a piece.}) 10. dxc6 {[%csl Rd1][%cal Gc6c7,Gc6b7] White threatens both [cxb7]+ and [c7]+, which would win back the sacrificed material with interest. Keep in mind that Black's bishop on [d1] is still hanging too.} a6 {Attacking the bishop doesn't solve Black's problems.} 11. c7+ {Opening the discovered check while attacking Black's queen with the pawn.} axb5 12. cxd8=Q+ Rxd8 13. Nxd1 $18 {White ends up being ahead a piece with a winning position. They were able to gain a big space advantage and then snowball this into a material advantage by taking advantage of a tactical opportunity.} *

