{In this example, we will see a situation where we begin with a space advantage and then transform this advantage into a material advantage later. First of all, White has more space in the center due to the [c4] and [d4]-pawns, while Black has no pawns on the fifth rank. White first begins by advancing further into Black's half of the board.} 11. d5 $1 {Advancing into Black's half of the board before they get to play ...[e5].} ({After} 11. Re1 $6 e5 12. d5 {± , White still has the advantage, but Black was able to get in the ...[e5] advance without repercussions.}) 11... Rac8 {Keeping the tension, but White can continue pressuring.} (11... e5 $2 {It's too late to make this advance.} 12. dxe6 $1 fxe6 13. Ng5 {, first we hit the [e6]-pawn.} Rfe8 14. Ba3 {, then the [d6]-pawn.} Nc5 15. b4 Ncd7 16. Nge4 {+- , Black's pawns are attacked from all angles.}) ({Trading pawns leads to a very pleasant position for White:} 11... cxd5 12. cxd5 {+- . Discovered attacks on the c-file are possible and [Nd4]-[c6] will come.}) 12. Nd4 $1 {Immediately putting maximum pressure on Black's [c6]-pawn. No matter how they deal with the pressure, they will have a bad position.} (12. Qd2 {was played in the game, but it is not as precise:} Nc5 13. Nd4 {± .}) 12... c5 $6 {Black tries to keep the c-file closed but this will cost them material.} (12... Nb8 {is probably Black's most resilient move, but it looks very depressing to move the knight back to its starting square.} 13. e4 {± and White has a huge space advantage.}) ({Trading pawns leads to a great position for White too:} 12... cxd5 13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14. cxd5 Qb8 15. Nc6 Bxc6 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. dxc6 {+- and the [c6]-pawn is very strong.}) 13. Ncb5 {[%csl Rc7][%cal Gb5c7,Gb5a7] Going after the queen first.} (13. Nc6 {, this move order works too:} Bxc6 14. dxc6 Ne5 15. Nb5 Qb8 16. c7 {+- .}) 13... Qb8 14. Nc6 {[%csl Ra7,Rb8,Re7][%cal Gc6b8,Gc6a7,Gc6e7] What a knightmare for Black!} Bxc6 15. dxc6 Ne5 16. c7 {[%csl Rb8][%cal Gc7b8] The queen is trapped and Black must sacrifice the exchange to save it.} Rxc7 17. Nxc7 $18 {White emerges ahead material with a big advantage. We were able to grow the space advantage, push pawns into Black's territory, and eventually win material due to their queen running low on squares.} *

