{What is the best way to play to transform our current long-term advantage into a new long-term advantage?} 18. h5 $16 {[%csl Rd4,Rg8][%cal Gh5h6,Gh5g6] It's time to attack! All of our pieces are well-placed and we have a central space advantage due to our [d4]-pawn. It is true that it's an isolated pawn, which can be a long-term liability, but for now, it's a useful asset for us since it helps control key central squares. We can use the h-pawn as a battering ram to help open the kingside. Our goal may be to play either [hxg6] to weaken their kingside pawn structure or [h6] to kick Black's bishop back to [h8] followed subsequently by a maneuver involving [Qf3] and [Bf6] to trade off a vital defender of Black's king.} *

