{What is the best way to play to transform our current long-term advantage into a new long-term advantage?} 7. d5 {We can press forward in the center and eventually win material using our space advantage.} exd5 8. cxd5 {[%csl Rc6,Re7][%cal Gd5c6,Gd5d6] Black has to respond to their knight being attacked, and we may be able to play [d6] afterwards to trap Black's bishop.} Nd4 {The only way to avoid losing a full piece is to sacrifice a pawn.} (8... Nb4 $2 {Black could try tying our queen down to defending the [c2]-square, but we will still end up winning material.} 9. d6 {, we still go forward to trap the bishop.} Bxd6 10. Qxd6 Nc2 {, Black has trapped our rook in the corner. Did we make a mistake?} 11. Qxc5 Nxa1 12. Be3 {+- , we lost our rook but will win back the knight soon since it is trapped. Then we will have two minor pieces vs. our opponent's rook, with a big advantage.}) 9. Nxd4 $18 {After Black recaptures, we can win the pawn on [d4] next. White has a big advantage with the extra pawn and space.} *

