{What is the best way to play to transform our current long-term advantage into a new long-term advantage?} 16... d4 $1 {[%csl Ra2,Rc3][%cal Ge6a2,Gd4c3] We have a tactic that's possible due to our space advantage in the center. White has two pieces under pressure simultaneously with the [c3]-knight and [a2]-bishop both being targeted.} 17. exd4 exd4 {[%csl Ra2,Rc3][%cal Gd4c3,Ge6a2] Continuing to make the same two threats.} (17... Bxa2 $4 18. dxe5 {± and now it's Black who has two threats to worry about! Both our [a2]-bishop and [f6]-knight are attacked. We will end up being down material in the near future.}) 18. Bxe6 dxc3 $19 {[%csl Rd2,Re6][%cal Gc3d2,Gf7e6] It's very important to capture the [c3]-knight first with this in-between move. White continues to have two pieces attacked on [e6] and [d2] and cannot avoid ending up down a piece.} *

