{What is the best way to play to start converting our long-term advantage?} 7. d4 $1 {Advancing in the center and getting rid of the weak [d4]-square is very good for White.} (7. Nc3 $6 {was played in the game, but it could have allowed Black to gain control of the [d4]-square.} Bg4 {∞ and White has a much harder time playing [d4] now.}) 7... Bd7 {Black breaks the pin but allows us to keep our d-pawn alive.} (7... exd4 $4 {Capturing this pawn would actually get Black into huge trouble, as White could open the center while Black's king remains uncastled.} 8. e5 $1 {Ignoring the [d4]-pawn and focusing on blasting open the e-file. After} dxe5 9. Nxe5 Bd7 10. Nxc6 Bxc6 11. Bxc6+ bxc6 12. Re1+ Be7 13. Bh6 {+- , Black will have a very difficult time finding a safe place for their king since we are preventing them from castling.}) 8. d5 $16 {[%csl Gc4,Gd5,Ge4][%cal Gd5c6] We gain an even bigger space advantage while kicking away Black's knight. After the knight moves, we could play [Bc2], avoiding a trade of bishops and leaving Black with cramped pieces due to their significant space disadvantage.} *

