{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 9... c4 $19 {[%csl Rb2,Rc4,Rd5][%cal Ga2a3,Gd4c5] It's best to sidestep the [d4]-pawn so that White's [b2]-bishop continues to be shut in. We gain a bigger space advantage and also avoid a weak isolated pawn of our own.} (9... cxd4 $6 {Trading pawns helps White to open their [b2]-bishop and gives us an isolated d-pawn. After} 10. Nxd4 Bg4 {∓ , Black still has the advantage, but there is no need to help White in the process.}) (9... Bg4 $2 {Slow moves could lose material.} 10. a3 $1 {Kicking our bishop away from defending [c5].} Ba5 11. dxc5 {∞ , White has won a pawn and the position is very unclear.}) *

