{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 16. e5 $1 {[%cal Ge5f6] Advancing the central pawns with tempo.} (16. d6 $4 {Pushing the d-pawn first doesn't work.} Qxd6 17. Rad1 Qc7 {-+ and Black is simply ahead a pawn.}) 16... Qg6 (16... cxd5 $4 {Capturing the pawn and attacking White's queen backfires.} 17. exf6 dxc4 18. fxe7 {+- and we end up ahead a piece.}) 17. d6 $18 {[%csl Gd6] Pressing forward with a threat on the knight this time. After the knight moves, we have two strong pawns that are far into Black's half of the board. The [d6]-pawn especially is a strong, protected passed pawn that will be a headache for Black to deal with.} *

