{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 11... Ba6 $17 {[%csl Ga6,Gg7][%cal Gf6f5] We have to go with a prophylaxis approach. It's very important to develop the light-squared bishop before White gets to play [a6] and completely restrict it. Next, we can play ...[f5] to open the other bishop.} (11... f5 $2 {A move like this is too slow and can get Black into trouble quickly:} 12. a6 {± . Our light-squared bishop is completely restricted and it will be very difficult to untangle our queenside pieces.} Nb8 $2 {Trying to target the [a6]-pawn doesn't work.} 13. Qd5 {+- , the rook on [a8] is hit and we have to put the knight back on [c6].}) *

