{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 11. f4 $1 {[%csl Rg6][%cal Gf4f5] White gains a larger space advantage while looking to trap Black's [g6]-bishop with [f5] next. Even after Black stops this with a move like ...[h6], we can still advance forward with [f5] to heavily restrict the bishop.} (11. d5 {⩲ was played in the game, which does give White a slightly better position but is not as precise. One downside to this move is that the bishop on [a7] has its diagonal opened up a bit more while our bishop on [g2] is shut in by the [d5]-pawn.}) *

