{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 13. f4 $16 {[%csl Gc4,Ge4,Gf4][%cal Gf4e5,Gd7e5] It's beneficial to gain more space while also preventing Black from playing ...[Ne5]. We restrict Black's knight from attacking the [c4]-pawn or maneuvering towards the [g4]-square. Our space advantage is very pleasant despite our slight king safety concerns with Black having the open h-file.} *

