{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 24. Qh3 $18 {[%csl Rh7] White has a space advantage in the center, which has been secured with the f-pawn. For that reason, it is now time to transfer pieces towards the opponent's king and start an attack. Black's [h7]-pawn is the target and they will need to create a weakness in their position in order to deal with our threat. Playing ...[g6] fails to [Bxg6]. After they play ...[h6], we could play [Qd3], threatening checkmate again. That would force Black to play ...[g5] and with these two pawn moves, Black has severely exposed their king and we gain a king safety advantage.} (24. Qd3 $6 {Attacking [h7] from this angle is okay but not as precise as [Qh3].} g6 {, it's a bit trickier for us to create additional weaknesses with this move order. If we play [Qh3] now, then Black can play ...[Kg8] and doesn't need to move another pawn in front of their king.}) *

