{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 7... d5 $19 {[%csl Gd5,Ge5][%cal Gf8e7,Ge8g8] We have a space and material advantage one extra pawn. We should gain more space in the center and prevent White from playing [c4] themselves. Next, we can focus on development and castling ASAP. Once that happens, we will have a huge advantage and White will have no compensation.} ({After} 7... Be7 $6 8. c4 $1 O-O 9. Nc3 {⩱ , Black is still better here with the extra pawn, but White has been able to equalize the space control and they also have a firm grip on our weak [d5]-square with us having a backward d-pawn too.}) *

