{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 19. h4 $16 {You could start with [Rad1] or [Rac1] first, but playing [h4] and working towards the pawn break on [h5] is a key part of White's plan revolving around using their space advantage and bishop pair. We want to go for a pawn break that weakens the opponent's kingside.} h5 $2 {If Black tries to stop the [h5] push, they can get themselves in huge trouble quickly.} (19... Bf8 {was played in the game.} 20. h5 {, White is not concerned about the pawn being captured because we can win it back easily.} Be7 21. Rad1 {+- and White has a big advantage across the board.}) 20. Bxg6 $1 {Sacrificing the bishop blasts open the king and gives White a big advantage.} fxg6 21. Qxg6+ Kf8 22. Qxe6 $18 {[%csl Rf8][%cal Gf4g5,Ge1e3,Ge3f3,Ge5e6] White has three pawns for the piece but more importantly, Black's king will never feel safe. We can play [Bg5], [Re3]-[f3], move the queen push the e-pawn, etc. Black has a very difficult task of defending and White is in great shape.} *

