{What is the best way to play to work towards converting our long-term advantage?} 8... d4 {Gaining more space in the center. We're also threatening ...[dxc3] followed by ...[Qxd3].} 9. cxd4 cxd4 $17 {It's important to recapture with the c-pawn. This maintains the space advantage without giving White as much counterplay. Next, we can develop our pieces and work towards queenside play later in the game.} (9... Nxd4 $2 {Recapturing with the knight allows White to trade a pair of pieces and unblock their f-pawn.} 10. Nxd4 {, trading pieces is good for the side that is behind on space.} cxd4 11. f4 {⩲ , White also gets this pawn break in against our center since they no longer have the knight on [f3] blocking the pawn.}) (9... exd4 $2 {Recapturing this way gives White a pawn break opportunity in the center towards our uncastled king.} 10. e5 $1 {White can sacrifice a pawn in the center since we are behind in development and not castled yet. After} fxe5 11. Re1 Bd6 12. Nc4 {± , White will win back the [e5]-pawn in the near future, and their lead in development and active pieces are dangerous for us.}) *

